Paging through the book, you realize that it is the journal of the unfortunate young man, now dead beside it.  Looking towards the back you read....

"...can't count days here, blasted cave.  I should have waited for my friends, now.. cut off like this.. I don't think I'll last much longer.  It's only a matter of time now until they find me.. death by goblins.. so distasteful.  I've found something strange down the passage though.  A series of entombed Goblin Chiefs.  Seems they have some strange fascination with preserving their old leaders... don't know what it means.. seems sinister at times though.  Last night they held some kind of ritual around them.. several priests.. came up from the central stairs, carryin' these giant mushrooms.. they started eating em.. crazed.. never saw anything like that.. frenzy... indescribable.  The intoxicated shrieking..  By the Gods!! I pray someone finds me before they do... they seem settled now though... perhaps I can get some sleep...."

A gleam of iron...
